# RentHub Frontend — Cursor Rules

## Project
Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui.
Web only. Portals: SYSTEM_ADMIN (/dashboard) and LANDLORD (/:pgId/*).
Tenant portal is mobile-only — never build web pages for TENANT userType.

## Absolute Rules (never violate these)
- Never use raw `fetch()` or `axios` directly in components or pages
- Never use `useState` to store data fetched from the API
- Never write inline status badge colors — always use `<StatusBadge status="..." />`
- Never render `internalNotes` in any component inside app/(tenant)/
- Never add `'use client'` unless the component uses hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- Never call Prisma or any backend logic from the frontend
- Never use `bg-[#hex]` or inline style for colors — use Tailwind palette classes only

## File Structure Rules
- API calls → src/lib/api/*.api.ts only (use apiClient from src/lib/api/client.ts)
- Zod schemas → src/lib/validations/*.schema.ts
- TanStack Query hooks → src/features/[feature]/hooks/use[Feature].ts
- Zustand stores → src/stores/*.store.ts (UI state only — sidebar, wizard step)
- Types → src/types/domain.types.ts (never redefine domain types inline)
- Common components → src/components/common/
- Feature components → src/features/[feature]/

## Data Fetching Pattern (always follow this)
- ALL server state → TanStack Query useQuery / useMutation
- Query keys → use featureKeys factory (e.g. leaseKeys.list(pgId, filters))
- After mutation success → call queryClient.invalidateQueries()
- Loading state → <LoadingSkeleton /> component (never a raw spinner div)
- Empty state → <EmptyState /> component
- Never use useEffect + useState to fetch data

## Form Pattern (always follow this)
- ALL forms → React Hook Form + zodResolver
- Schema defined in src/lib/validations/ first, then z.infer<> for the type
- Submit button → disabled + show loading state while mutation is pending
- Errors → inline below each field via formState.errors

## Styling Rules
- Tailwind classes only — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use cn() from src/lib/utils.ts for conditional classes
- Color usage: primary-700 for solid bg, primary-100/200 for badge bg, primary-50 for hover tint
- shadcn/ui components for all UI primitives (Button, Input, Dialog, Sheet, etc.)
- Never hand-roll a modal — use shadcn Dialog or Sheet

## Auth Rules
- Route protection lives in src/middleware.ts only — not in page components
- Use useAuth() hook from src/hooks/useAuth.ts to read current user
- userType TENANT → redirect to /mobile-only, never render portal pages
- userType SYSTEM_ADMIN → /dashboard routes only
- userType LANDLORD → /:pgId/* routes only

## TypeScript Rules
- strict mode is on — no `any`, no type assertions unless absolutely necessary
- All API response types come from src/types/domain.types.ts
- DTOs (form submit types) come from z.infer<typeof schema>
- Never use `as unknown as X` to silence TypeScript errors — fix the type properly